Clarke Leads Johnson by One Stroke After Third Round of British Open Golf

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-07-16T18:15:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-16/clarke-leads-johnson-by-one-stroke-in-third-round-of-golf-s-british-open.html
Northern Ireland ’s Darren Clarke
holds a one-stroke lead over Dustin Johnson of the U.S. after
three rounds of golf’s British Open.  Clarke shot 1-under-par 69 today at Royal St. George’s in
Sandwich, England, to reach 5-under for the championship.
Johnson finished with 68 to move into second at 4-under.  American Rickie Fowler also shot 68 and is 2-under, along
with Denmark’s Thomas Bjorn, who had a 1-over-par 71. Spain’s
Miguel Angel Jimenez and Lucas Glover of the U.S. are the only
other players below par at 1-under. Four-time major champion
 Phil Mickelson  is among six golfers at even-par.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  